deselectNet(25.10)                                          deselectNet(25.10)

Name
       deselectNet - Deselects the specified net

Syntax
        deselectNet

       [-help]

       [<netName>]

       [-clock | -nonDefaultRule | -shield ]

       Deselects  the specified net. Once a net is deselected, it is no longer
       highlighted in the design display window. Run this  command  after  se-
       lecting one or more nets.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deselectNet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deselectNet

       <netName>
              Specifies the name of the net you want to deselect.  You  cannot
              specify  more  than  one  net. You can, however, use a wild card
              (*).

              Data_type: (net)*, optional

       -clock Deselects all nets that have a DEF attribute + USE CLOCK.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -nonDefaultRule
              Deselects all nets that have a DEF attribute + NONDEFAULTRULE.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -shield
              Deselects all nets that have a DEF attribute + SHIELDNETS.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Examples
              * The following command deselects the net named net_1:

                deselectNet net_1

              * The following command deselects all clock nets:

                deselectNet -clock

Related Information
              * deselectAll

              * selectNet

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

